{"title":"2022 Orbea Rallon gets mullet option, heaps of frame storage and new geometry","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/10/2022-orbea-rallon-gets-mullet-option-heaps-of-frame-storage-and-new-geometry/","date":1631279332000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084923/2022-orbea-rallon-night-riding-berm-dust-cloud-lit-up-800x534.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"2022 orbea rallon night riding berm dust cloud lit up\" loading=\"eager\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-271004\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>The 2022 Orbea Rallon rolls out on 29″ wheels, or, a 27.5″ wheel in the rear with a 29″ wheel up front. That’s <em>sort of</em> two bikes for the price of one, given that they run the same frame; you just swap out the rear wheel and use the supplied shock extender to convert to a mullet without dramatically altering the geometry. Also new for this model year is the addition of frame storage, and it comes fully equipped with tools stored in the rear axle and main pivot.</p><h2>2022 Orbea Rallon</h2><ul><li>Intended Use: Enduro / Big Mountain / Park</li><li>Frame Material: OMR Carbon</li><li>Fork Travel: 170mm</li><li>Rear Wheel Travel: 160mm</li><li>Wheel Size: 29er or Mullet&nbsp;</li><li>Starting Price: $4,999 USD</li></ul><div id=\"attachment_271099\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271099\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea rallon m10 29er blue white carbon frame\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085527/2022-orbea-rallow-m10-29er-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271099\">The 2022 Orbea Rallon M10 retails at $5,999 USD (29er configuration shown)</p></div><p>At first glance, the 2022 Orbea Rallon doesn’t look strikingly different to its 2020 iteration. The suspension layout is very familiar, still running that asymmetrical front triangle where the shock mounts at the top tube. It is still composed of Orbea’s OMR Carbon layup with a slight adjustment to the tune to give it a little more vertical compliance for traction over rough camber. Geometry is still adjustable too, with low and lower settings to choose from giving riders the option to switch between 64° and 64.5° head tube angles.</p><p>The big news for this model year is that Orbea are now supplying shock extenders with the purchase of each bike that will allows riders to switch out the 29″ wheel for a 27.5″ wheel to run a mullet configuration. Of course, you could have done this on the 2020 frame, but the addition of the shock extender allows you to do so without dramatically affecting the geometry.</p><div id=\"attachment_271098\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271098\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea rallon m-team yellow mullet\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085055/2022-orbea-rallon-yellow-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271098\">The 2022 Orbea Rallon M-Team retails at $7,299 USD (Mullet configuration shown)</p></div><p>The only notable geometry differences between the full 29er and the Mullet would be the 5mm shorter reach, 2mm shorter effective chainstay length and decreased standover. Orbea don’t provide low and lower geometry figures for the mullet, stating a bottom bracket height of 343mm, the same as the 29er in its “low” position.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea rallon suspension linkage layout\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085723/2022-orbea-rallon-suspension-linkage-layout-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>For the 2022 Rallon, Orbea are pushing their new “steep and deep” geometry concept which largely refers to the fact that the frame is now designed around a 200mm dropper post. The terrain gets steep, so you push the saddle deep… you get the idea. Permitting that are the (largely) shorter, steeper seat tubes, that are now straight and uninterrupted.</p><div id=\"attachment_271100\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea rallon fox x2 air shock\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10085718/2022-orbea-rallon-fox-x2-air-shock-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271100\">The 2022 Rallon can accommodate both air and coil shocks</p></div><p>Taking the XL as an example, the seat tube is now 23mm shorter than that seen on the earlier iteration of the Rallon, measuring up at 460mm. The small is the only frame in the size range to see a longer seat tube for 2022, now sitting at 415mm, the same as the size medium. This is pretty long, actually, given that it isn’t unusual to see 380mm seat tubes on small bikes these days.</p><div id=\"attachment_271080\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271080\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures.jpg\" alt=\"2022 ORBEA RALLON 29ER MULLET GEOMETRY CHARTS\" width=\"1600\" height=\"773\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures-297x143.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures-800x387.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures-120x58.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures-768x371.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures-1536x742.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures-297x143.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures-800x387.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures-120x58.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures-768x371.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10075307/2022-Orbea-Rallon-29er-mullet-geometry-figures-1536x742.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271080\">Editor’s Note: Orbea have mistakenly switched the seat tube angle and standover rows, so watch out for that.</p></div><p data-wp-editing=\"1\">I almost forgot… those seat tubes are also considerably steeper, sitting at 77° in the “lower” setting, and 77° in the “low” setting (and on the mullet). That change is likely to improve the climbing characteristics of the bike, especially for riders of the larger frame sizes making use of ultra long travel dropper posts.</p><div id=\"attachment_271091\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10081653/2022-orbea-rallon-leverage-curve.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271091\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10081653/2022-orbea-rallon-leverage-curve.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea rallon leverage ration versus 2020 frame\" widt