amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10081653/2022-orbea-rallon-leverage-curve-1536x910.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271091\">Orbea describe the 2022 Rallon as “Linear Progressive” with a leverage ratio of 22-33%</p></div><p data-wp-editing=\"1\">While the locations of the pivots haven’t changed dramatically, subtle differences have made for a more progressive use of the 160mm of rear wheel travel. The key takeaways here are that higher starting ratio for improved suppleness off the top, and the increased end-stroke progression for better bottom-out resistance. The kinematic changes likely make the frame better suited to the linear spring rate of a coil shock.</p><p data-wp-editing=\"1\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea rallon anti-rise anti-squat versus 2020 frame comparison\" width=\"1600\" height=\"475\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs-297x88.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs-800x238.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs-120x36.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs-768x228.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs-1536x456.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs-297x88.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs-800x238.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs-120x36.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs-768x228.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084042/2022-orbea-rallon-anti-rise-anti-squat-graphs-1536x456.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p data-wp-editing=\"1\">Orbea say they have made these changes to the leverage curve without dramatically impacting the braking and pedaling characteristics of the bike. <em>“Anti-rise and anti-squat are kept largely the same because our racers love the way the bike remains active under braking and sprints out of slower speed turns”</em> – Orbea. Taking a look at the anti-rise comparisons, seems to me the anti-rise changes, at least during the early to mid-stroke, are quite significant. Basically, anti-rise is a metric used to describe how well a bike’s rear suspension remains active under breaking. You can read about it in depth <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/10/04/suspension-tech-what-is-anti-rise/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a>.</p><p data-wp-editing=\"1\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea rallon rear axle path\" width=\"1600\" height=\"914\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path-297x170.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path-800x457.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path-120x69.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path-768x439.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path-1536x877.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path-297x170.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path-800x457.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path-120x69.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path-768x439.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10084658/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-path-1536x877.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p data-wp-editing=\"1\">Those subtle pivot location changes have also brought about a change to the rear axle path, allowing the axle to track a more rearward path to around the sag point, from which it then tracks forwards.</p><h3 data-wp-editing=\"1\">In-Frame Tool Storage!</h3><p>Here’s the fun bit. The 2022 Orbea Rallon actually comes equipped with some tools, so you can ride out knowing you’ve not forgotten everything you need for basic trail side repairs.</p><div id=\"attachment_271092\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271092\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea rallon flp multitool sotred inside main pivot magnetic\" width=\"1600\" height=\"899\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage-120x67.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage-1536x863.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage-800x450.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage-120x67.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10082319/2022-orbea-rallon-flp-multi-tool-frame-storage-1536x863.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271092\">A magnet hold the FLP multi-tool inside the main pivot cavity</p></div><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10083646/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-bottle-opener.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10083646/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-bottle-opener.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea rallon bottle opener rear axle\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10083646/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-bottle-opener.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10083646/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-bottle-opener-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10083646/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-bottle-opener-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10083646/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-bottle-opener-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10083646/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-bottle-opener-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10083646/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-bottle-opener-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10083646/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-bottle-opener.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10083646/2022-orbea-rallon-rear-axle-bottle-opener.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/10083646/2022-orbea-rallon-re